{
  "feature_id": "define-approval-and-clarify-persistence-semantics",
  "phase": "impl",
  "current_round": 2,
  "status": "in_progress",
  "max_finding_id": 10,
  "findings": [
    {
      "id": "R1-F01",
      "severity": "high",
      "category": "completeness",
      "file": "src/core/advance.ts",
      "title": "No ClarifyRecord handling in advance.ts",
      "detail": "The spec requires ClarifyRecord creation when a clarify question is issued and auto-resolution when a clarify_response is received (spec: 'Clarify record is created when a clarify question is issued', 'Clarify record is auto-resolved when response is received'). The advance.ts implementation only handles ApprovalRecord creation/update — there is zero clarify record logic. Add handling for clarify_request (create pending ClarifyRecord) and clarify_response (resolve existing ClarifyRecord) events.",
      "origin_round": 1,
      "latest_round": 1,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": "",
      "resolved_round": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "R1-F02",
      "severity": "high",
      "category": "correctness",
      "file": "src/core/advance.ts",
      "title": "event_ids never populated on record update",
      "detail": "The spec states 'the event_id of the approval event SHALL be appended to event_ids' on decision, and similarly for clarify. The implementation copies existing event_ids with `event_ids: [...pending.event_ids]` but never appends any new event_id. Since AdvanceInput does not carry an event_id, either (a) AdvanceInput needs an optional event_id field, or (b) the core runtime needs to generate one. As-is, event_ids will always remain empty, violating the N:1 event-to-record cardinality requirement.",
      "origin_round": 1,
      "latest_round": 1,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": "",
      "resolved_round": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "R1-F03",
      "severity": "medium",
      "category": "completeness",
      "file": "src/core/advance.ts",
      "title": "Actor provenance missing from history entries",
      "detail": "The workflow-run-state spec requires each history entry to include `actor` (kind) and `actor_id` fields: 'Each history entry SHALL include actor provenance'. The RunHistoryEntry type and the history construction in advance.ts do not include these fields. Either extend AdvanceInput to carry actor identity and thread it into history, or document this as explicitly deferred.",
      "origin_round": 1,
      "latest_round": 1,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": "",
      "resolved_round": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "R1-F04",
      "severity": "medium",
      "category": "correctness",
      "file": "src/core/advance.ts",
      "title": "decision_actor hardcoded to null on approval/rejection",
      "detail": "The spec states 'decision_actor set to the acting actor identity' when a decision is made. Lines 155 and 171 hardcode `decision_actor: null` with comment 'Actor identity is not available in core runtime'. This means the ApprovalRecord will never record who made the decision, even when the information could be threaded through AdvanceInput. If actor identity threading is intentionally deferred, the spec scenario 'Approval record is updated when decision is made' is violated.",
      "origin_round": 1,
      "latest_round": 1,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": "",
      "resolved_round": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "R1-F05",
      "severity": "medium",
      "category": "scope",
      "file": "openspec/changes/archive/",
      "title": "Whitespace-only reformatting of 10+ archived JSON files",
      "detail": "The diff includes 10+ archive review-ledger/task-graph JSON files with purely cosmetic changes (2-space indent → tab indent). These changes are unrelated to the approval-clarify-persistence feature and inflate the diff. Either revert them or split into a separate formatting commit.",
      "origin_round": 1,
      "latest_round": 1,
